  "text": "Our model concept does not separate the autotrophic and the heterotrophic components of soil respiration. More importantly, however, it separates the temperature-and the carbon allocation driven parts of the respiration, with the temperature driven part including both the heterotrophic and autotrophic response. Similarly, the carbon allocation driven part includes some heterotrophic respiration (priming) due to the root exudation in the rhizosphere [CITATION_1] .",
